I was tired of folks telling me what kind of bad cosmetic procedures I “shouldn’t have had done to myself.” My body needs a whole detox and cleanse after having to take so much stuff in 30 days. I shoulda planned this out better. Lesson learned. System overload!

I know I’ve talked incessantly about the weight gain I experienced in the past 4 years and many of yall have told me it was all in my head (and some have more than validated that I had “fell off”. Umm thanks!) well I wasn’t delusional but what I WAS doing was not showing the unflattering photos and  was only posting pics where u couldn’t tell I had gained over 25 pounds! When taking pics or even just being out in public I’d constantly be sucking my stomach in and arching my back so damn hard it hurt! Well I wanted to share my progress with you all in this #reel 
Also a reminder to anyone else struggling with weight gain…. It’s NOT easy and there will be days where u feel like you’ll never get there—- but there are so many things out there COMBINED with hard work that can assist you. Take advantage of it all. Good luck 💋🙏🏾 
P.S. the shots I was on was #Ozempic and your doctor can prescribe it after a check up and getting blood work done. It wasn’t cheap but totally worth it FOR me. I  was at my wits end and running /walking up to 7 miles a day got my heart in shape but the weight wasn’t going anywhere. Plus I snacked WAY too much! It totally suppressed my appetite
Shelly!! 17 years and counting! Nothing but love here! 💙P.S. pets have good discernment when it comes to people. I’m just saying 🤷🏽‍♀️💙

Friends and family- I want  to acknowledge someone who’s relentless hard work and dedication behind the scenes hasn’t been said enough and all too often gets over shadowed by the viral moments and the noise but not today!  Today I salute James DuBose- has been in the game behind the scenes of so many of your favorite iconic shows! Well now this Brother can add successfully leading a whole network for THREE YEARS to his long list of accomplishments. We recently celebrated 3 years of success and growth here at Fox Soul and I  don’t feel right with us acknowledging the network but not the MAN behind the network that has burdens and stresses that we will never know! But yet we stay the course (his favorite quote to encourage all of us.) I’m sure it has been difficult to maneuver and there’s been so many fires to put out and things that needed to be done to make things as smooth as they are for the viewers and the talent that our minds couldn’t even wrap around and for that James I want to publicly thank and salute you for making it all look so easy. Cause I’m sure it is not. Yet you make it do what it does without ever letting us see you sweat or hear you complain-and for that Black man— I wanna give you your props! Many have tried… few are still standing. And that’s cause of your leadership and on behalf of the entire Fox Soul family we salute you!! THANK YOU James!!!!! Three down…. Decades to go!! 💪🏾🙌🏾🙏🏾🙌🏾💫⭐️💫📈

Last summer was my last summer in my 40’s and I LIVED and it was beautiful. But I made a promise to myself that I’d cross a lot of things off my bucket list and I feel THIS year is extra special and a huge milestone. For the first time in my life I’m gonna try to see what it feels like to prioritize my own needs and feelings to ensure a SOFT LIFE for myself from here on out into the final chapters. Cause why not?? 🤷🏽‍♀️
The unknown can be viewed as scary OR it can be viewed as extremely exciting and a chance for a rebirth/ reintroduction. 
Your path and conditions all depend on YOUR mindset and THAT is a choice. I choose to be fearless as opposed to being scared and have my growth stunted and paralyzed by fear. Last year I jumped  out there on a couple of things…. Professionally, personally and financially-and I  regret very little of it cause it came from a pure place and I’m proud of that. There were highs, lows, revelations and major triumphs! And Im still here hopefully inspiring someone watching to KEEP going!! Don’t ever quit! Set goals and picture them as already here and real. One of the things I promised myself a year ago was that I  wasn’t going to go another birthday NOT living in MY house (I’ve been in high rise apts for the past 12 years pretty much) I claimed I’d be moving into a house by my 50th b day and I’m happy to share that TOMORROW I  close on a beautiful big home in Dallas!! I  want y’all to know how much power lies in your thoughts and is manifested  by your tongue! Claim what you want/ picture it, visualize it and put energy and real effort into getting what you want and it WILL be YOURS. You can’t just be idle and think it will come to YOU. That’s lazy and arrogant. Stay humble, consistent and be very intentional and you WILL see it come to fruition. You can do it!!! 💋💋💋💋💋

The history. 26 years ago… @corporatebarbie_ invited me on a trip to Mexico where she introduced me to her long time friend @mimifaust 
We immediately hit it off! Shortly after Mimi and I became roommates for one year in LA when we were about 24 years old still trying to figure out Life. 
I met @corporatebarbie_ in 1994 when we both were in this International Women of Color fashion show in Boston and she was an up and coming banker. The DAY I met her I was like “I like this girl’s style, swag and confidence!” Well… The rest is history. We’ve been there for weddings, divorces, annulments, babies, breakups, heartbreaks and thinking one of us have “found the ONE (again)! 😇” 
Thru all the highs and the lows things haven’t never gotten funny or weird. Just three women supporting  each other Thru the decades with pure intentions to be nothing but real and down for each other. I love these two ladies and I’m so grateful to have them both in my life. These are 2 of my “lifers”. They say you’re lucky if you have just 2 real ones. And I def have that and some! Love you both! 🙌🏾🙌🏾🙌🏾❤️

🥰🥰🥰🥰🥰 This is 50. 
Don’t be afraid or look down upon aging. And it’s dumb to call someone “old” that’s actually doing what they’re supposed to be doing in this world. Aging means you’re still here and you made it thru some things. The alternative to NOT aging is no longer existing, no longer growing and no longer LIVING. Live your life loud and unapologetically. We are the authors of our own stories and I’d you don’t like the direction you’ve been going in/ edit, adjust and reroute!  Make sure as you get closer to the end of this thing called life- you have less regrets about what you didn’t get to do and more memories of the things you’re glad you went for and tried! Life is not all about the best THINGS… it’s all about the best experiences. Know that! 💕💕😇😍#Aries

We spent several years side by side creating the most entertaining, shocking, real, unique and original content for radio far before the podcasts and shows came after us that were no doubt inspired by what we created on the FoxxHole. These were different times before the world became overly sensitive and lost it’s sense of humor. We all understood it was never hate/ just wildly inappropriate jokes. This show and the group you handpicked was genius and you KNEW.

I often tell people you’re the best storyteller on earth and your talent knows no bounds. I’ve literally watched you make a song about anything on the spot and you had no ego unlike most stars when it came  to allowing us to make fun of you on the air. People couldn’t see this cause there were no cameras but you’d be waving it on encouraging us to come at your neck like “come on/ go harder! Go deeper!” (On the jokes !) you never got mad cause your instincts told you it was good for the show and you were right! No one did it like the FoxxHole- because of YOU @iamjamiefoxx !!!

Outside of the radio show and the Coors Light commercials we did together -We were most definitely like family for the longest. When I  couldn’t make it back east for holidays your house and family always welcomed me with open arms. I for real felt like you were the cousin I never had! So many memories !! Watching you cry during Castaway when Wilson floated away and how you let me roast you the next day on air was my favorite!! 😂😂😂 such a good sport! “Well you know Jamie hates to see anything white go!” 😂😂

I am praying for your  100% full and speedy recovery Jamie, you are loved, admired and your light has and always will shine bright from the impact you’ve made. Love and light Foxx. Can’t wait to get you say again “What’s cracking? Other than the crack of ya ____!” 
@iamjamiefoxx

Yes I AGREE the Democrats have always done a horrible job with self promotion and bragging about accomplishments but that’s what Google is for before you ask this very annoying question. I have followed this woman since she was running for office many moons ago in California. We got to interview her on the FoxxHole and I followed her career as the ONLY black woman in the senate where she used to light they azzes up fighting for us! As far as this narrative that she’s done all@these horrible things to black men and locked them up by targeting them/ it’s just not true. Please go to YouTube and search the video on @rolandsmartin page. He had a guest in there that so eloquently debunked all of that WITH facts and receipts not just “I heard…” this woman has had to work twice as hard for 1/10th of the respect and we owe it to her to at LEAST look up the facts on her before sending all this vitriol her way. It breaks my heart to see a woman—- and especially a sister be dragged like this and all too often by our very own! We have got to do better! You don’t have to live her—- but you don’t have to lie on her either. She’s busy! Trust!!

From Miss Teen Rhode Island 1990 to the Miss Teen USA pageant… to runner up in Miss Ohio (while in college) to winning Miss Rhode Island (on my 3rd try) and making the top 10 at the Miss USA pageant in 1997!!! Then I got asked to judge Miss USA and Miss Universe before getting the dream job of actually HOSTING the Miss UNIVERSE pageant! Talk about a full circle moment!! Definitely grateful for how this small town girl’s life (from East Providence, Rhode Island) turned out! And we ain’t done! And it all started with a model search booth in the Rhode Island Mall in like 1989/1990 that I thought was just a John Casablanca’s modeling school scam. But taking a chance and saying YES lead me to where I am now! So the lesson is to BE OPEN TO ALL OPPORTUNITIES big and small and to STAY HUMBLE and always keep it cute cause you JUST never know where a grateful heart and a positive attitude willing to WORK hard will take you!!! And I’m NOWHERE near where I want to be STILL but I’m working on it!

The one thing about longevity is you’re around long enough to witness friend’s growth. Me and @theonlyjasonlee used to hang tight 14 years ago. We were 2 peas in a pod and have stories for days! Fun fact (before the Breakfast Club and all these other highly successful shocking radio shows and podcasts and fresh off the heels of my time on The FoxxHole where i did 4 years of very raw comedy  radio with @iamjamiefoxx ) We once recorded a pilot episode for a radio show with us, @cthagod and @thelilmoshow called “The Funeral” and let me just tell you… after we leaked just one clip that got 2 million hits in 4 days we knew we’d be a PROBLEM (and we were all destined for greatness!!) Well the Universe said Aht Aht Aht- this is TOO much recklessness for the people to handle at the same time (Charla booked the breakfast club like a few weeks later) so we all had to figure something else out. This made us all have to get creative and find another path. And boy did @theonlyjasonlee do just that! Fast forward to current times and he’s now one of the hugest names in his lane and the creator and CEO of @hollywoodunlocked and so much more!! I tell you all the time Jason how proud I am of you! Yes it wasn’t always smooth sailing -but here we are! Im happy to celebrate you and witness the fruits of your hard work! Hoping this is the happiest of birthdays and this year gives you even more!! Happy Birthday friend! ❤️❤️❤️

I’m so disgusted. 1st at the man who’s ego was so fragile his ego he couldn’t accept this woman not wanting her to give him her number. And secondly- by the group of men who stood around & watched this woman get her face smashed in! Sadly- this isn’t all that uncommon! It’s just that most women keep it to themselves & just deal with it and have adapted & usually just tell the man what he wants to hear until she can get outta the situation safely!! Women are being scared into just relinquishing their numbers & then dealing with the man later by blocking or curving them. Ladies—- how have y’all dealt with an overly aggressive man that asked for your number or to go out? Have you ever been really scared or even injured cause you turned down a man’s advances?  I’ll share first. One of my early concussions came at the hands of a man who insisted on giving me his number after I told him several times I was spoken for. I was 21 years old & in Providence, Rhode Island on summer break from college. After not calling him I ran into him at a club & he pulled my arm so hard & yelled “why didn’t you call me!?” I responded “I told you I was already seeing someone & I wasn’t going to call!” And I snatched my arm back & walked off. Moments later a very strong forced pushed me hard as hell snapping my neck back & it was him. He pushed me to the floor. I stood up & faced him & all I remember was him cocking his arm back & a tussle. I do not remember being  punched in the back of my head. My friend Heather was panicking & screaming OMG Claudia I cant believe he hit you!! I said “no he didn’t!” I went home & went to sleep. The next morning I woke up with the worst pain in the back of my neck & head & went straight to the ER where they gave me X-rays to see if my teeth were cracked. I guess I experienced a standing knock out or something & my memory has been trash ever since! FYI NOTHING happened to this man despite me going to the police cause he was friends w/them all and in the process of trying to become a state trooper!! After that I changed the way I dealt with men hitting on me. I’m not alone in this. Many women play the game to survive. Praying for her speedy recovery. 💔😞

Prioritize taking  care of your body and your credit in your 20’s, (build that cardio and strengthen your heart and lungs). Focus on your business and loyal friends in your 30’s- (save money and start investing) and really figure out what and who makes YOU happy. Make sure you stay hydrated and protect your hairline and your assets in your 40’s (prioritize self care, vacations and YOU time) and your 50’s will have you looking well preserved and stress free! And never ever ever ever stay in some relationship sh*t or a situationship if you start questioning your own worth and you don’t feel heard. The world really tries to shame women that choose to NOT tolerate someone’s dusty son’s mistreatment and instead choose to live a peaceful and happy life unmarried. Don’t let them! Not saying love isn’t a priority cause it is- and who wouldn’t want THAT?? I know I  do! And I’d love to be a wife again-But if you’re feeling bad more than good- and unsure and unsafe- choose YOU until the right one makes his presence and intentions known. In other words don’t settle for just anything just to say “you got a man.” When you’re happy and whole- you radiate a different kind of energy that the good ones pick up on! Trust! Stay beautiful and open minded ladies! Muah! 💋
